Basic ideas of coding conventions that we try to follow:

C++ formatting is ensured by:
    find src \( -name "*cpp" -or -name "*hh" \) -print -exec /home/ljanin/net/astyle/build/gcc/bin/astyle --style=allman --indent-switches --pad-paren-in --pad-header --align-pointer=name --align-reference=name --lineend=linux --indent-col1-comments --min-conditional-indent=0 {} \;

Details: See http://astyle.sourceforge.net/astyle.html
  --style=allman
  --indent-switches 
  --pad-paren-in 
  --pad-header 
  --align-pointer=name 
  --align-reference=name 
  --lineend=linux 
  --indent-col1-comments
  --min-conditional-indent=0


Coding conventions matching Illumina's Software Engineering:
- Variable names should follow "thisStyle"
- Private class member should end with an underscore

